A motorcyclist declared dead at the scene of an accident was found alive in a morgue the next day, but he died later in hospital. A motorcyclist declared dead at the scene of an accident was found alive in a morgue fridge the next day when his family went to identify his body, but he died later in hospital.The victim, who was not identified, was injured in a crash on a road in the southeastern province of KwaZulu-Natal, and was transferred to the morgue in Durban.The next morning, however, mortuary staff detected a pulse and breathing and rushed him to hospital, where doctors and nurses managed to resuscitate and warm him, but he later died, according to a health department official.KwaZulu-Natal health authorities said they had launched an investigation into the incident. The passing away of any individual is a painful experience, a provincial health department statement said. The department can confirm that an internal inquiry is under way. 